We recommended that Management to:
Submit explanation why the eight projects were not implemented during the year despite the availability of sufficient funds;
Properly plan the implementation of all PPAs funded out of the 20% DF to avoid delays and ensure 100% accomplishment within a particular period;
Instruct the DF Focal Person to conduct regular coordination before the Budget Cycle with the concerned offices to identify all project requirements and exert utmost effort to ensure that PPAs are implemented within the target period; and
Henceforth, strictly observe the guidelines on the appropriation and utilization of the 20% DF under DILG-DBM JMC No. 2017-1 dated February 22, 2017.

We recommended that the City Mayor require the Head, Social Services Department to:

Conduct investigation to determine the cause of discrepancies in the payrolls totaling P312,000.00 and P5,480,000.00 on the issue of double payments and on the perceived receipt of benefits by illegitimate beneficiaries, respectively;

Submit Official Receipt (OR) representing the amount of  P9,168,000.00 as proof of refund for those payees who did not claim/receive the cash/payment but were included in the payroll;

Submit the above listed supporting documents to the Auditor for further audit of the liquidation payrolls totaling P75.89 million; and

Ensure that future payments are made only to eligible and legitimate beneficiaries of SAP as identified by the DSWD and supported with proper and complete documents/ information.

We reiterated our prior years’ recommendation that the City Mayor require:

The MCCPPEID to - 

Reconcile their records with the AO to determine the causes of discrepancies; 


The Head of the AO   to - 

Reconcile property ledger cards with the records of the MCCPPEID to maintain complete and updated property ledger cards; 

Verify and analyze the identified discrepancies and errors and make   necessary adjustments in the books of accounts; 

