Analyze the balance of the Due to other NGAs account and reclassify to their appropriate accounts, including the negative balance, to correct the balances of the affected accounts;
Exert best efforts to locate the documents pertaining to the dormant  accounts to determine the nature of the payables and establish their validity;
Confirm with the source agencies the SL balances in the books, reconcile the dormant accounts, and make adjustments as necessary; and
Remit immediately to the National Treasury and/or source agency the unutilized/unexpended fund balances.

We recommended that the City Mayor require the Head, MSP to:
Review and evaluate the PayMaya Disbursement System, its strengths and weakness, to determine their capability to handle the project;
Conduct orientation about the disbursement systems of PayMaya with the parents of the beneficiaries for them to be  able to have a full grasp of the system;
Negotiates/accept proposals into the services of other Government Authorized Depository Banks that can efficiently handle the distribution/disbursement system with the least cost charges to the beneficiaries; and
Follow up with PayMaya the immediate return of the unclaimed amounts to the City.
